The national executive of Brazil'smost militant trade union group has proposed a general strikefor July 15 in protest at the government's austerity program.    A spokeswoman for the Workers' Confederation, CUT, toldReuters today that the proposal would be discussed within thetrade union movement.    On Friday the government of President Jose Sarneyintroduced austerity measures to try to combat the country'shigh inflation rate, currently running at more than 1,000 pct ayear.    The new plan scrapped a "trigger" mechanism which hadguaranteed regular pay rises in line with high inflation.    Trade unions say real wages are dropping by about a third. Reuter&#3;